<%#
===================================================================================
                    INDEX.EJS - All Listings Page (Home)
===================================================================================

ðŸ“š WHAT IS THIS FILE?
---------------------
This is the MAIN LISTINGS PAGE that displays all hotel properties.
It shows a responsive grid of cards, each representing a hotel listing.

ðŸ”— ROUTE: GET /listings
   Data passed: { allListings } (array of all listings from MongoDB)

ðŸ“Œ EJS CONCEPTS:
---------------
- <% %>: Execute JavaScript (no output)
- <%= %>: Output escaped HTML (safe from XSS)
- <%- %>: Output unescaped HTML (use carefully!)
- <%# %>: Comment (not rendered)

ðŸ“Œ BOOTSTRAP GRID:
-----------------
- .row-cols-lg-3: 3 cards per row on large screens
- .row-cols-md-3: 3 cards per row on medium screens  
- .row-cols-sm-1: 1 card per row on small screens (mobile)

ðŸ“Œ FOR LOOP:
-----------
<% for(let listing of allListings) { %>
  ... render each card ...
<% } %>

ðŸ“– INTERVIEW TIP:
----------------
"I used EJS templating to dynamically render hotel listings from MongoDB.
The responsive grid uses Bootstrap's row-cols classes to automatically
adjust the number of cards per row based on screen size. Each card links
to the detailed show page using the MongoDB ObjectId."

===================================================================================
%>
<% layout("layouts/boilerplate") -%>
<body>
  <h3>All Listings</h3>
  
  <%# Responsive Grid: 3 cols on lg/md, 1 col on sm (mobile) %>
  <div class="row row-cols-lg-3 row-cols-md-3 row-cols-sm-1">
  
  <%# Loop through all listings from database %>
  <% for(let listing of allListings) { %>
    <%# Each card links to its detail page using MongoDB _id %>
    <a href="/listings/<%=listing._id%>" class="listing-link">  
      <div class="card col">
        <%# Hotel image with fixed height %>
        <img src="<%=listing.image%>" class="card-img-top" alt="Listing_Image" style="height: 20rem">
        
        <%# Overlay text on hover (styled in CSS) %>
        <div class="card-img-overlay">Smart Stay</div>
        
        <%# Card content: title and price %>
        <div class="card-body">
          <p class="card-text">
            <b><%= listing.title %></b><br>
            <%# &#8377; = Rupee symbol, toLocaleString formats with commas %>
            &#8377;<%= listing.price.toLocaleString("en-IN") %> /night
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </a>
  <% } %>
  
  </div> 
</body>
